Data Preprocessing & Exploratory Data Analysis - Pearson Correlation Coefficient¶

$$ \text{Pearson Correlation Coefficient:} \quad r_{X,Y} = \frac{\sum_{i=1}^n (x_i - \bar{x})(y_i - \bar{y})} {\sqrt{\sum_{i=1}^n (x_i - \bar{x})^2} \, \sqrt{\sum_{i=1}^n (y_i - \bar{y})^2}} $$

Data Preprocessing & Exploratory Data Analysis - Autocorrelation¶

$$ \text{Autocorrelation:} \quad r_k = \frac{\sum_{t=1}^{N-k} (x_t - \bar{x})(x_{t+k} - \bar{x})} {\sum_{t=1}^{N} (x_t - \bar{x})^2}, \quad k = 0,1,2,\dots $$

Data Preprocessing & Exploratory Data Analysis - Stationarity¶

$$ \text{ Augmented Dickey-Fuller (ADF) Test:} \quad \Delta y_t = \alpha + \beta t + \gamma y_{t-1} + \sum_{i=1}^p \delta_i \Delta y_{t-i} + \varepsilon_t, \quad H_0: \gamma = 0, \; H_1: \gamma < 0 $$

$$ \text{Kwiatkowski–Phillips–Schmidt–Shin (KPSS) Test:} \quad y_t = r_t + \beta t + \varepsilon_t, \quad \text{KPSS} = \frac{1}{T^2 \hat{\sigma}^2} \sum_{t=1}^T S_t^2 $$

FCON - Statistical & Time Series Modelling¶

--

Statistical & Time Series Modelling - Residual & Normality Testing¶

$$ \text{Ljung–Box Test: } \quad Q=n(n+2)\sum_{k=1}^{h}\frac{\hat\rho_k^{2}}{n-k}\sim\chi^2_{\nu},\ \nu=h-d \qquad \text{Shapiro–Wilk Test: } \quad W=\frac{\left(\sum_{i=1}^{n} a_i x_{(i)}\right)^2}{\sum_{i=1}^{n}(x_i-\bar{x})^2},\ \bar{x}=\frac{1}{n}\sum_{i=1}^{n}x_i $$

--

Statistical & Time Series Modelling - Model Evaluation¶

$$ \text{Akaike Information Criterion: } \quad \mathrm{AIC}=-2\log(\hat L)+2k \qquad \text{Bayesian Information Criterion: } \quad \mathrm{BIC}=-2\log(\hat L)+k\log n $$

$$ \text{Mean Error: } \quad \mathrm{ME}=\frac{1}{n}\sum_{t=1}^n e_t \quad \qquad \text{Mean Percentage Error: } \quad \mathrm{MPE}=\frac{100}{n}\sum_{t=1}^n \frac{e_t}{y_t} \qquad $$

$$ \text{Root Mean Squared Error: } \quad \mathrm{RMSE}=\sqrt{\frac{1}{n}\sum_{t=1}^n e_t^{2}} \quad \qquad \text{Mean Absolute Percentage Error: } \quad \mathrm{MAPE}=\frac{100}{n}\sum_{t=1}^n \left|\frac{e_t}{y_t}\right| $$

$$ \text{Mean Absolute Error: } \quad \mathrm{MAE}=\frac{1}{n}\sum_{t=1}^n |e_t| \quad \qquad \text{Mean Absolute Scaled Error: } \quad \mathrm{MASE}=\frac{\frac{1}{n}\sum_{t=1}^n |e_t|}{\frac{1}{T-m}\sum_{t=m+1}^{T} |y_t-y_{t-m}|} $$

--

Forecasting - Holt-Winters’ Exponential Smoothing (Additive Seasonality)¶

$$ \begin{aligned} \ell_t &= \alpha(y_t - s_{t-m}) + (1-\alpha)(\ell_{t-1}+b_{t-1}) \quad & b_t &= \beta(\ell_t - \ell_{t-1}) + (1-\beta)b_{t-1} \\ s_t &= \gamma(y_t - \ell_t) + (1-\gamma)s_{t-m} \quad & \hat y_{t+h\mid t} &= \ell_t + h\,b_t + s_{t-m + h^\ast},\; h^\ast = 1 + ((h-1)\bmod m) \end{aligned} $$

In [ ]:
forecastincomehw <- hw(uschangeTraining[,"Income"], h = 7, 
                       seasonal = "additive")
forecastunemploymenthw <- hw(uschangeTraining[,"Unemployment"], h = 7, 
                             seasonal = "additive")
